rComments: Amazing teacher! Makes learning fun rather than tedious and uninteresting. Doesn't really give homework, mostly just quizzes, creative reflections, videos, etc. Super easy class - stress free. She just never - and i mean ever - answers her emails so if you have something to ask, ask it in class.

Very understanding of current world circumstances and will work with her class to make sure everyone is feeling comfortable (little to no stress for this class). Very engaging and knowledgeable about content. Classes are fun and her way of instilling language is creative.

Literally one of the best profs I've ever had. She is so kind and understanding. The class content is so interesting and fun. Nothing better than a down-to-earth prof and great class content. She makes learning fun!

She's my kind of person. Great people skills. She cares that you pass. Show up to class, take notes and you will have an easy A, even A+. No readings. She adapted well to zoom classes. She keeps it interesting. Didn't feel sleepy at all during her class (it was a 3h zoom class), so that speaks for itself! Overall amazing!

Sam is the best! The class was elementary Algonquin language learning and definitely the most fun I've had in a uni course so far. She uses a lot of visuals and oral reinforcement which makes it easy to learn (as long as you practice!) I would suggest making flashcards for this course and doing them on your commute to school
